  <Docs>
    <summary>Holds font selection arguments including variation position, palette selection, and collection index.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct used to pass font customization parameters to methods
such as <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>. It can specify a
variation design position, a color palette index, per-entry palette color overrides, and
a font collection index.

This is a value type and requires no disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
};
using var cloned = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
